30  package sun.nio.cs.ext;
31  
32  import java.nio.CharBuffer;
33  import java.nio.ByteBuffer;
34  import java.nio.charset.Charset;
35  import java.nio.charset.CharsetDecoder;
36  import java.nio.charset.CharsetEncoder;
37  import java.nio.charset.CoderResult;
38  import sun.nio.cs.HistoricallyNamedCharset;
39  
40  public class IBM33722
41      extends Charset
42      implements HistoricallyNamedCharset
43  {
44  
45      public IBM33722() {
46          super("x-IBM33722", ExtendedCharsets.aliasesFor("x-IBM33722"));
47      }
48  
49      public String historicalName() {
50          return "Cp33722";
51      }
52  
53      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
54          return (cs instanceof IBM33722);
55      }
56  
57      public CharsetDecoder newDecoder() {
58          return new Decoder(this);
59      }
60  
61      public CharsetEncoder newEncoder() {
62          return new Encoder(this);
63      }
64  
65  
66      /**
67       * These accessors are temporarily supplied while sun.io
68       * converters co-exist with the sun.nio.cs.{ext} charset coders
69       * These facilitate sharing of conversion tables between the
70       * two co-existing implementations. When sun.io converters
71       * are made extinct these will be unncessary and should be removed
72       */
73  
74      public String getDecoderSingleByteMappings() {
75          return Decoder.byteToCharTable;
76      }
77  
78      public String getDecoderMappingTableG1() {
79          return Decoder.mappingTableG1;
80      }
81  
82      public String getDecoderMappingTableG2() {
83          return Decoder.mappingTableG2;
84      }
85  
86      public String getDecoderMappingTableG3() {
87          return Decoder.mappingTableG3;
88      }
89  
90      public short[] getEncoderIndex1() {
91          return Encoder.index1;
92  
93      }
94      public String getEncoderIndex2() {
95          return Encoder.index2;
96      }
97  
98      public String getEncoderIndex2a() {
99          return Encoder.index2a;
100     }
101 
102     public String getEncoderIndex2b() {
103         return Encoder.index2b;
104     }

106     protected static class Decoder extends CharsetDecoder {
107 
108         private final int G0 = 0;
109         private final int G1 = 1;
110         private final int G2 = 2;
111         private final int G3 = 3;
112         private final int G4 = 4;
113         private final int SS2 =  0x8E;
114         private final int SS3 =  0x8F;
115 
116         private int firstByte, state;
117 
118         public Decoder(Charset cs) {
119                 super(cs, 1.0f, 1.0f);
120         }
121 
122         private CoderResult decodeArrayLoop(ByteBuffer src, CharBuffer dst) {
123             byte[] sa = src.array();
124             int sp = src.arrayOffset() + src.position();
125             int sl = src.arrayOffset() + src.limit();
126             assert (sp <= sl);
127             sp = (sp <= sl ? sp : sl);
128             char[] da = dst.array();
129             int dp = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.position();
130             int dl = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.limit();
131             assert (dp <= dl);
132             dp = (dp <= dl ? dp : dl);
133 
134             try {
135             while (sp < sl) {
136                 int byte1, byte2;
137                 int inputSize = 1;
138                 char outputChar = '\uFFFD';
139                 byte1 = sa[sp] & 0xff;
140 
141                 if (byte1 == SS2) {
142                     if (sl - sp < 2) {
143                         return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
144                     }
145                     byte1 = sa[sp + 1] & 0xff;
146                     inputSize = 2;
147                     if ( byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {   //valid first byte for G2
148                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
149                     }
150                     outputChar = mappingTableG2.charAt(byte1 - 0xa1);
151                 } else if(byte1 == SS3 ) {                 //G3
152                     if (sl - sp < 3) {
153                         return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
154                     }
155                     byte1 = sa[sp + 1] & 0xff;
156                     byte2 = sa[sp + 2] & 0xff;
157                     inputSize = 3;
158                     if ( byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {
159                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
160                     }
161                     if ( byte2 < 0xa1 || byte2 > 0xfe) {
162                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(3);
163                     }
164                     outputChar = mappingTableG3.charAt(((byte1 - 0xa1) * 94) + byte2 - 0xa1);
165                 } else if ( byte1 <= 0x9f ) {                // valid single byte
166                     outputChar = byteToCharTable.charAt(byte1);
167                 } else if (byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {   // invalid range?
168                     return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
169                 } else {                                     // G1
170                     if (sl - sp < 2) {
171                         return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
172                     }
173                     byte2 = sa[sp + 1] & 0xff;
174                     inputSize = 2;
175                     if ( byte2 < 0xa1 || byte2 > 0xfe) {
176                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
177                     }
178                     outputChar = mappingTableG1.charAt(((byte1 - 0xa1) * 94) + byte2 - 0xa1);
179                 }
180                 if  (outputChar == '\uFFFD')
181                     return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(inputSize);
182                 if (dl - dp < 1)
183                     return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
184                 da[dp++] = outputChar;
185                 sp += inputSize;
186             }
187             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
188             } finally {
189                 src.position(sp - src.arrayOffset());
190                 dst.position(dp - dst.arrayOffset());
191             }
192         }
193 
194         private CoderResult decodeBufferLoop(ByteBuffer src, CharBuffer dst) {
195             int mark = src.position();
196             try {
197                 while (src.hasRemaining()) {
198                     int byte1, byte2;
199                     int inputSize = 1;
200                     char outputChar = '\uFFFD';
201                     byte1 = src.get() & 0xff;
202 
203                     if (byte1 == SS2) {
204                         if (!src.hasRemaining())
205                             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
206                         byte1 = src.get() & 0xff;
207                         inputSize = 2;
208                         if ( byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {   //valid first byte for G2
209                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
210                         }
211                         outputChar = mappingTableG2.charAt(byte1 - 0xa1);
212                     } else if (byte1 == SS3 ) {                 //G3
213                         if (src.remaining() < 2)
214                             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
215 
216                         byte1 = src.get() & 0xff;
217                         if ( byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {
218                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
219                         }
220                         byte2 = src.get() & 0xff;
221                         if ( byte2 < 0xa1 || byte2 > 0xfe) {
222                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(3);
223                         }
224                         inputSize = 3;
225                         outputChar = mappingTableG3.charAt(((byte1 - 0xa1) * 94) + byte2 - 0xa1);
226                     } else if ( byte1 <= 0x9f ) {                // valid single byte
227                         outputChar = byteToCharTable.charAt(byte1);
228                     } else if (byte1 < 0xa1 || byte1 > 0xfe) {   // invalid range?
229                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
230                     } else {                                     // G1
231                         if (src.remaining() < 1)
232                             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
233                         byte2 = src.get() & 0xff;
234                         if ( byte2 < 0xa1 || byte2 > 0xfe) {
235                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
236                         }
237                         inputSize = 2;
238                         outputChar = mappingTableG1.charAt(((byte1 - 0xa1) * 94) + byte2 - 0xa1);
239                     }
240 
241                     if (outputChar == '\uFFFD')
242                         return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(inputSize);
243                     if (!dst.hasRemaining())
244                         return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
245                     dst.put(outputChar);
246                     mark += inputSize;
247                 }
248                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
249             } finally {
250                     src.position(mark);
251             }
252         }
253 
254         protected CoderResult decodeLoop(ByteBuffer src, CharBuffer dst) {
255             if (true && src.hasArray() && dst.hasArray())
256                 return decodeArrayLoop(src, dst);
257             else
258                 return decodeBufferLoop(src, dst);
259         }
260
